Omg, this slapped so hard. Zahoor sounded really good, and when Rehma came in with them vocals, I was shook. For some reason, the female vocals in Coke studio songs always shake me more than the males. Like in Season 14 when we had Quratulain Baluch, Arooj Aftab, Naseebo Lal & Abida Parveen, Shae Gill, Meesha Shafi, Justin Bibis and in Season 15 we have Marvi-Saiban and Rehma.

Edit forgot the ones who sang Maghron La (I think Sabri Sisters)

snippet.textDisplay: What a brilliant fusion! The emotional depth conveyed is heart-warming. I don’t understand Pashto, but you can still connect with the feelings and sentiments expressed through tone, melody, and delivery. Never imagined how both languages complement and harmonize with each other, creating a rich and textured sonic landscape. The  traditional instruments or contemporary Western arrangements, each element contributes to the song’s overall atmosphere and mood. Congratulations to the amazing vocalists and of course Xulfi and his incredible team! You guys are legend! Thank you for yet another masterpiece. 🙌🏽💕

snippet.textDisplay:
Coke Studio 15 is all about showing our culture. Full credit for this.
Ayi Ayi - Sindhi
Maghroon La - Punjabi
Harkalay - Pakhtoon

As for the song, the girl giving the vibes of Havana by Camila. ✅
The boy is giving vibes of Jay Sean. ✅

Overall, this song giving vibes of 2000s music. Nothing new. ❌

The only good song in this season so far is "2AM". That was something new, music & videography wise. 💓
